<title>USA: System Software Associates Q1 Jan 31 loss widens.</title>
<headline>System Software Associates Q1 Jan 31 loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>System Software Associates Inc said Thursday substantially higher expenses caused a wider loss in the first quarter ended January 31.</p>
<p>The company reported a net loss of $4.3 million, or $0.10 a share, compared to a loss of $400,000, or $0.01 a share in the year-ago period.</p>
<p>Revenues improved to $92.2 million from $76.6 million.</p>
<p>System Software said the higher expenses were in part related to investments in research and development.</p>
<p>The company develops software for the industrial sector.</p>
<p>Its shares closed down 1/4 Thursday at 10-1/4.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
